5 SECTION 14. IC 21-42-5-4, AS AMENDED BY P.L.120-2013,
6 SECTION 5, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
7 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 4. The core transfer library shall be developed in
8 accordance with the following principles:
9 (1) Each course in the core transfer library must transfer in and
10 apply toward meeting degree requirements in the same way as the
11 receiving state educational institution's equivalent course.
12 (2) Courses in the core transfer library must draw from the liberal
13 arts and introductory or foundational courses in technical,
14 professional, and occupational fields that are part of the single
15 articulation pathways established under IC 21-42-6-4.
16 (3) At least seventy (70) courses must be identified for inclusion
17 in the core transfer library. The identified courses must emphasize
18 the courses most frequently taken by undergraduates.
19 (4) With respect to core transfer library courses being transferred
20 from a state educational institution to Indiana University or
21 Purdue University, Indiana University and Purdue University
22 must identify transfer equivalents so that a course accepted by one
23 (1) regional campus is accepted by all other regional campuses
24 that offer the same transfer equivalent course.
25 (5) Within the Indiana University system and Purdue University
26 system, equivalent courses, including courses with the same
27 course number and title, must count in the same way at all
28 campuses within the system where the course is offered.
29 (6) A state educational institution shall award course credit
30 for a satisfactory score (as defined in IC 20-36-1-4) on an
31 advanced placement examination in which the advanced
32 placement examination corresponds to the state educational
33 institution's course in the core transfer library.
34 (7) With respect to course credit awarded by a state
35 educational institution for a satisfactory score (as defined in
36 IC 20-36-1-4) on an advanced placement examination that
37 corresponds to the state educational institution's course on the
38 core transfer library, a receiving state educational institution
39 must transfer and apply course credit in alignment with the
40 receiving state educational institution's corresponding course
41 in the core transfer library or as elective credit if no
42 corresponding course is offered in the core transfer library.
ES 204—LS 6843/DI 143

