1 SECTION 15. IC 21-44-8 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
2 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]:
4 Chapter 8. Health Profession Education Program
5 Sec. 1. This chapter does not apply to a contract entered into or
6 renewed before July 1, 2026.
7 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "health profession education
8 program" means an education program that:
9 (1) is designed to prepare a student for a career in a health
10 profession regulated by an entity described in IC 25-0.5-11;
11 and
12 (2) requires a student to complete clinical training or clinical
13 experience at an offsite facility.
14 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "immunization" means the
15 treatment of an individual with a vaccine to produce immunity.
16 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "student" means a student
17 enrolled in a health profession education program.
18 Sec. 5. A student may not be required to receive an
19 immunization as a condition of:
20 (1) participating in; or
21 (2) obtaining;
22 clinical training or clinical experience required by a health
23 profession education program if a parent of the student, if the
24 student is an unemancipated minor, or a student, if the student is
25 an adult or emancipated minor, objects on religious grounds.
26 SECTION 16. [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026] (a) 25 IAC 5-6-3(b) is
27 void. The publisher of the Indiana Administrative Code and
